-1 STORY~
.{&
In the beginning of the realm, there came a light in the vast darkness of
the condition known as existence.  The one known as F'nor came and claimed
the lands around as his own.  He was kind, and the light he brought was
very appreciated by the masses of people that had been living in darkness
for so long.  F'nor, and his dragon Canth, were Gods in the eyes of those
around.  But there was one who remembered the darkness.  One who found the
light to be oppressing, and not as benevolent as those around.  Her heart
was as pitch, black and thick with hatred.  This one was Ezmirel.
     Ezmirel had seen how F'nor did his tricks and powers, and soon taught
herself to emulate those powers, although she could not match F'nor's power
in those skills.  She planned to overthrow F'nor and return the world to
the state of darkness it was before, the way she remembered and loved.
Unfortunately for Ezmirel, the people of the realm as a whole did not
wish to return to those days as she did.  A very few agreed with Ezmirel,
but most all sided with F'nor.  Ezmirel grew very angry, and took to very
violent acts and subterfuge to spread her ideas about the absence of
light.  She slandered the light, and spread lies saying it was evil, but
the people saw through her attempts at deception, and grew to hate her 
even more.  Finally Ezmirel just threw herself totally against F'nor,
thinking that with F'nor out of the way, she would be able to rule
completely, and the people would grow to love her just as much as they now
loved F'nor.
     F'nor loved the people he had brought out of the darkness, and he
could not bring himself to stand by and watch this Ezmirel attack some of
these people just because they liked it better light.  F'nor decided that
even though he loved peace, this one must be pacified one way or the
other.  He tried to talk to this hater of light, but Ezmirel just threw
hate back in his face, and even tried to bring about F'nor's death, which
Canth saved him from.  So F'nor, under advice from some of his closest new
friends, decided that he had to fight back.
     There came a time one fine bright day, when Ezmirel just all out
attacked F'nor.  She did this in front of a multitude of people.  F'nor had
been advised to expect this by some who knew of Ezmirel before F'nor's
arrival, so he was fully ready.  F'nor had learned of Ezmirel's power and
made himself immune to that attack, and struck back at Ezmirel with a
fierce power of his own.  Ezmirel was caught totally unaware by the
ferocity of this attack by the normally peaceful F'nor.  F'nor totally
decimated Ezmirel that day, and Ezmirel, defeated soundly, retreated to
recover her wounds, and pride.
     F'nor knows that Ezmirel was not beaten permanently, as she was always
too tenacious in her hatred, but for the time being, Ezmirel has been
pacified.  There will most likely come a time when Ezmirel feels prepared
enough to strike again, but until that time, the Light reigns supreme,
and F'nor is still most loved by the people of the realm.

