-1 THERA STORY~
.{&In the beginning of the realm, there came a light in the vast darkness of
the condition known as existence.  The one known as F'nor came and claimed
the lands around as his own.  He was kind, and the light he brought was
very appreciated by the masses of people that had been living in darkness
for so long.  F'nor, and his dragon Canth, were Gods in the eyes of those
around.  But there was one who remembered the darkness.  One who found the
light to be oppressing, and not as benevolent as those around.  His heart
was as pitch, black and thick with hatred.  This one was Ezmeril.
     Ezmeril had seen how F'nor did his tricks and powers, and soon taught
himself to emulate those powers, although he could not match F'nor's power
in those skills.  He planned to overthrow F'nor and return the world into
the state of darkness it was before, the way he remembered and loved.
Unfortunately for Ezmeril, the people of the realm as a whole did not
wish to return to those days as he did.  A very few agreed with Ezmeril,
but most all sided with F'nor.  Ezmeril grew very angry, and took to very
violent acts and subterfuge to spread her ideas about the absence of
light.  She slandered the light, and spread lies saying it was evil, but
the people saw through his attempts at deception, and grew to hate him
even more.  Finally Ezmeril just threw herself totally against F'nor,
thinking that with F'nor out of the way, she would be able to rule
completely, and the people would grow to love her just as much as they now
loved F'nor.
     F'nor loved the people he had brought out of the darkness, and he
could not bring himself to stand by and watch this Ezmeril attack some of
these people just because they liked it better light.  F'nor decided that
even though he loved peace, this one must be pacified one way or the
other.  He tried to talk to this hater of light, but Ezmeril just threw
hate back in his face, and even tried to bring about F'nor's death, which
Canth saved him from.  So F'nor, under advice from some of his closest new
friends, decided that he had to fight back.
     There came a time one fine bright day, when Ezmeril just all out
attacked F'nor.  He did this in front of a multitude of people.  F'nor had
been advised to expect this by some who knew of Ezmeril before F'nor's
arrival, so he was fully ready.  F'nor had learned of Ezmeril's power and
made himself immune to that attack, and struck back at Ezmeril with a
fierce power of his own.  Ezmeril was caught totally unaware by the
ferocity of this attack by the normally peaceful F'nor.  F'nor totally
decimated Ezmeril that day, and Ezmeril, defeated soundly, retreated to
recover his wounds, and pride.
     F'nor knows that Ezmeril was not beaten permanently, as he was always
too tenacious in his hatred, but for the time being, Ezmeril has been
pacified.  There will most likely come a time when Ezmeril feels prepared
enough to strike again, but until that time, the Light reigns supreme,
and F'nor is still most loved by the people of the realm.{x
~
